        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/zetabeta/{size}/54310_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-12T20:24:54.289Z",
        "cooked": "<p>i am investigating this issue. signal desktop may have complicated bug. my information is partial.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Geobert\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74180\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/geobert/48/48588_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Geobert:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I\u2019ve migrated from Gnome to Niri, on NixOS, and since, I have an error asking me to start with <code>\u2013password-store=\"gnome-libsecret\"</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>linux distributions have feature called \u201corg.freedesktop.secrets\u201d. which is dbus service, where a program can register as a secrets storage. basically there is three options.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p># pacman -Ss org.freedesktop.secrets<br>\nextra/gnome-keyring 1:48.0-1 (gnome)<br>\nStores passwords and encryption keys<br>\nextra/keepassxc 2.7.11-1<br>\nCross-platform community-driven port of Keepass password manager<br>\nextra/kwallet 6.21.0-1 (kf6)<br>\nSecure and unified container for user passwords</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>desktop environment usually boots up default program and possibly opens storage automatically.</p>\n<p>desktop environment may have no secrets program at all.</p>\n<p>signal desktop uses secrets storage. if one is not available, then signal can store keys internally to appdata folders.</p>\n<p>if signal gets access to secrets storage afterwards, it moves into that secrets storage. however, it won\u2019t move back into internal storage if secrets storage disappears, which i think is bad.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Geobert\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74180\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/geobert/48/48588_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Geobert:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Doing so makes Signal asking my session password in order to start.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>it seems that gnome-libsecret is not started automatically.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Geobert\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74180\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/geobert/48/48588_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Geobert:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>So, can I put the password-store thingy in config.json?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>in my knowledge, no.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Geobert\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74180\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/geobert/48/48588_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Geobert:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>How do I avoid the password prompt?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>i don\u2019t know good fixes for this.</p>\n<p>if you relink signal desktop with destroying appdata, you may go internal storage. but do not start signal desktop in gnome system.</p>\n<p>partial solution could be using keepassxc, which has some other issues.</p>",
